"26:60:2" : {s: 26, a: 60, w: 2, r: "شرق", t: "مُّشْرِقِينَ", l: "مُّشْرِقِين", lc: 2, tl: "mush'riqīna", lb: "",e: "(at) sunrise", b: "সুর্যোদয়কালে", f: 1, rm: "to split, rise, slit. sharqiyyun - of or pertaining to the east, eastern. mashriq - place of sunrise, east. mashriqain - two easts/horizons, two places where the sun rises (in winter and summer, East and West). mashaariq - different points of sunrise, whence the sun rises in the course of the year, beam, gleam, eastern parts. ashraqa (vb. 4) - to shine, rise. ishraaq - sunrise. mushriqun - one on whom the sun has risen, who does anything at sunrise, one entering at the sunrise."},
